`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The codebase uses Two raycasting philosophies: **Rapier** (`world.castRay`) for physics-accurate hits against terrain trimesh colliders (already used in `useJump`), and **Three.js** `Raycaster` for entity detection against visual meshes tagged with `mesh.userData.entityId`. The acceptance criteria says "Rapier raycast from camera" but the entity meshes (trees, NPCs) don't have Rapier colliders — only terrain does. This is the key architectural question.
