`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- **Three.js Raycaster vs Rapier castRay**: Entity meshes (trees, NPCs) use `mesh.userData.entityId` on individual `THREE.Mesh` objects — Three.js `Raycaster.setFromCamera(Vector2(0,0), camera)` is the right tool. Rapier `castRay` only works against explicit Rapier colliders (only terrain has those).
- **Screen-center ray**: `setFromCamera(new Vector2(0, 0), camera)` fires a ray exactly from camera position along camera forward — this is the standard FPS targeting pattern in R3F.
- **Testability pattern**: Export pure functions (`resolveEntityById`, `findNearestStructure`) that take iterables instead of module-level queries — same pattern as `isGrounded` in `useJump.ts`.
