`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- **Rapier vs Three.js for entity targeting**: The story title says "Rapier raycast" but entity meshes (trees, NPCs, structures) have no Rapier colliders — only terrain trimesh does. `THREE.Raycaster.setFromCamera(Vector2(0,0), camera)` correctly fires from camera position along forward, which is the actual intent.
- **InstancedMesh blind spot**: `StructureInstances` uses `InstancedMesh` with no per-instance `userData` — a spatial `findNearestStructure` fallback handles this without changing the renderer.
- **Testable seams via iterable injection**: Passing `Iterable<Entity>` parameters instead of module-level query refs enables direct array injection in tests — zero Miniplex mocking required.
